text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia subflexuosa is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Peel and Wheatbelt regions of Western Australia.The dense shrub typically grows to a height of 0.25 to 1 metre (1 to 3 ft). It blooms from August to September and produces yellow flowers.
There are two recognised subspecies:

Acacia subflexuosa subsp. capillata
Acacia subflexuosa subsp. subflexuosa
